cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the theoretical basis of the covariance matrix adaptation evolution strategy (CMA-ES) in the context of information geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper also touches upon optimization and statistics, which could place it in cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories, respectively.
